laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT-guided left upper quadrant mass biopsy

findings.soft_tissues: 8.7 x 6.2 x 7.6 cm well-circumscribed, lobulated, predominantly T2 hyperintense mass with hairline thin T2 hypointense septations. Mild delayed enhancement.
findings.liver: Homogeneous in signal characteristics, no solid or cystic lesions.
findings.biliary: No intra- or extra-hepatic duct dilatation.
findings.pancreas: Normal bulk, no focal lesion or ductal abnormality.
findings.spleen: Normal in size and signal characteristics.
findings.kidneys: Normal in size and signal characteristics, no hydronephrosis.
findings.vasculature: Patent without significant areas of narrowing or dilatation.
findings.osseous_and_soft_tissue_structures: Bone marrow demonstrates normal signal characteristics.
